# Navigation

This project uses **react-navigation v7** with two navigators:

- **Stack Navigator** (root) — wraps the tab navigator and hosts stack-only screens (e.g. `Detail`)
- **Bottom Tab Navigator** — hosts the main tabs: Home, Search, Notification, Settings, AIChat

## Screen Name Registry

All screen name strings live in a single constant. **Never** use raw string literals for screen names.

File: `src/shared/constants/index.ts`

```typescript
export const SCREENS = {
  ROOT: "Root",
  HOME: "Home",
  SEARCH: "Search",
  NOTIFICATION: "Notification",
  SETTINGS: "Settings",
  DETAIL: "Detail",
  AI_CHAT: "AIChat",
  // add new screens here
};
```

## Adding a New Tab Screen

1. Add the key to `SCREENS` in `src/shared/constants/index.ts`
2. Create the screen in `src/screens/<name>/<Name>Screen.tsx` + `<Name>Screen.style.ts`
3. In `src/navigation/index.tsx`:
   - Import the screen component
   - Add a `case SCREENS.<NAME>:` in `renderTabIcon` returning the correct icon name
   - Add `<Tab.Screen name={SCREENS.<NAME>} component={<Name>Screen} />`

```typescript
// renderTabIcon switch
case SCREENS.MY_SCREEN:
  iconName = focused ? "icon-filled" : "icon-outline";
  break;

// Tab.Navigator
<Tab.Screen name={SCREENS.MY_SCREEN} component={MyScreen} />
```

## Adding a New Stack Screen

Stack-only screens (pushed on top of the tab navigator, e.g. detail/modal views):

```typescript
// src/navigation/index.tsx
<Stack.Navigator screenOptions={{ headerShown: false }}>
  <Stack.Screen name={SCREENS.ROOT} component={renderTabNavigation} />
  <Stack.Screen name={SCREENS.DETAIL}>
    {(props) => <DetailScreen {...props} />}
  </Stack.Screen>
  <Stack.Screen name={SCREENS.MY_MODAL} component={MyModalScreen} />
</Stack.Navigator>
```

## Imperative Navigation (from outside components)

Use `react-navigation-helpers` — the `navigationRef` is already wired up in the `NavigationContainer`:

```typescript
import { navigate, push, goBack } from "react-navigation-helpers";

// Navigate to a screen
navigate(SCREENS.DETAIL);

// Push with params
push(SCREENS.DETAIL, { id: "123" });

// Go back
goBack();
```

The `isReadyRef` is set to `true` in `NavigationContainer.onReady` — safe to call these after that.

## Theme-Aware Navigation Container

The navigator automatically switches between `LightTheme` and `DarkTheme` based on the system color scheme:

```typescript
const scheme = useColorScheme();
const isDarkMode = scheme === "dark";

<NavigationContainer theme={isDarkMode ? DarkTheme : LightTheme}>
```

Both themes are exported from `@theme/themes`. The tab bar background also switches automatically via:
```typescript
tabBarStyle: { backgroundColor: isDarkMode ? palette.black : palette.white }
```

## Screen Component Template

```typescript
import React, { useMemo } from "react";
import { View } from "react-native";
import { useTheme } from "@react-navigation/native";
import { SafeAreaView } from "react-native-safe-area-context";
import createStyles from "./MyScreen.style";

const MyScreen: React.FC = () => {
  const theme = useTheme();
  const styles = useMemo(() => createStyles(theme), [theme]);

  return (
    <SafeAreaView style={styles.container}>
      {/* screen content */}
    </SafeAreaView>
  );
};

export default MyScreen;
```
